cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.DB

The paper deals with the forensic analysis of an instant messaging application on Android smartphones, which involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and databases (cs.DB). The focus on encryption and decryption techniques, as well as the analysis of stored data, suggests that cs.CR is the most likely sub-category. However, the use of emulated devices and experimental methodology also involves aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The emphasis on privacy and security also suggests the relevance of cybersecurity (cs.CY), while the analysis of stored data involves aspects of databases (cs.DB).
